sourcesContent:
const modalList = [ 
  {
    buttonImage: require("../../Images/discord.png"),
    modalvideo: require("../../videos/Typr.mov"),
    modalTitle: "Discord Clone",
    technologies1: require("../../Images/firebase.png"),
    technologies2: require("../../Images/React.png"),
    technologies3: require("../../Images/html5.png"),
    technologies4: require("../../Images/sass.png"),
    site: "https://scratch-paint.netlify.app/",
    modalDescription: `In this project, I make my own version of the discord chat app. 
    Where you can actually log in and talk to other authenticated users. Front-end using 
    React and for the backend Firebase for the database. I wanted to teach myself more 
    about databases and this project definitely did that.`
  },
  {
    buttonImage: require("../../Images/scratch.png"),
    modalvideo: require("../../videos/scratchVideo.mov"),
    modalTitle: "Scratch-Paint",
    technologies2: require("../../Images/React.png"),
    technologies3: require("../../Images/html5.png"),
    technologies4: require("../../Images/sass.png"),
    site: "https://scratch-paint.netlify.app/",
    modalDescription: `Scratch-Paint is a hackathon group project. In the hackathon, 
    the challenge was to create a paint app. This project showed me the importance of 
    communication of team goals. Using Jira to make sure everyone is on the same page 
    and proper branch management. This was my first group project with a designer. 
    Which showed me having a designer is a must going forth`
  },
  {
    buttonImage: require("../../Images/instock.png"),
    modalvideo: require("../../videos/instock.mov"),
    modalTitle: "InStock",
    technologies2: require("../../Images/React.png"),
    technologies3: require("../../Images/html5.png"),
    technologies4: require("../../Images/sass.png"),
    site: "https://scratch-paint.netlify.app/",
    modalDescription: `InStock is a warehouse site made with my BrainStation classmates. 
    We used React for the front-end and a node js express server for the backend. 
    This project was incredibly valuable. We used a Jira board. Which taught me 
    so much about dividing tasks among the group. Also learned about merging and 
    dealing with conflicts with other people's codes.`
  },
  {
    buttonImage: require("../../Images/speed.png"),
    modalvideo: require("../../videos/instock.mov"),
    modalTitle: "In Stock",
    technologies2: require("../../Images/React.png"),
    technologies3: require("../../Images/html5.png"),
    technologies4: require("../../Images/sass.png"),
    site: "https://scratch-paint.netlify.app/",
    modalDescription: `Speed-Typr was my first React solo project 
    for the last day of the BrainStations 3 month dev program. On 
    project day I received the most business cards in the class from 
    recruiters. Recruiters were more impressed that a carpenter could 
    learn and apply so much to a project without having any experience of code.`
  },
];

export default modalList;
